1 lb. flank steak
salt & black pepper
4 Tbsp butter, divided
1 med onion, thinly sliced
1.5 Tbsp minced shallots
8 oz. large shiitake mushrooms, stemmed, thinly sliced
pita

1/2 c mayo
1/4 c prepared white horseradish
black pepper

In a small bowl, combine mayo and horseradish.  Season to taste with salt &
pepper.

Pat steak dry and season both sides well with salt & pepper

Metl 1 Tbsp butter in large heavy skillet over medium-high heat.  Add steak
to skillet and cook for about 5 minutes on each side.  Transfer meat to
cutting board and let stand for 5 minutes.

In the same skillet, melt 3 Tbsp butter over medium-high heat.  Add onions
and shallots; saute until golden brown.  Add mushrooms and saute until
tender, about 5 minutes.  Season to taste with salt & pepper.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Spread horseradish mayo on pita, add steak, then top with onion/mushroom
mixture.
